* The lights in Desmonus's face caused her to momentarraly shut her optics, 
her bat senses reeling. An annoyed hiss escaped her lips as she tryed to 
wriggle in her confinement, trying desperatly to get away from this light 
the almost seemed to eat away at her very soul!
Her wings stretched out on either side of her as she wriggled and squirmed.
However, every action proved useless until she was finally fed up, opening 
her mouth and emitting a high pitched bat screem.
Raising the pitch until, above, ever light in the room as well as every 
glass piece of equipment shattered.
The lights dimmed for a moment until finally going out, a sigh of relief 
coming from the fembot strapped to the table.
THAT was better.
She would have raised her head to look around but there was a strap across 
her neck as well, however, that wasn't the only way that she could see.
With short little squeeks she sent little shock waves around the room, the 
waves bouncing off of objects and returning to her with information about 
the object it had bounced from.
It's size, shepe and depth.
The picture of the whole room forming in her mind from the info she 
gathered.
This strange room wasn't all that big, but it was large enough to house a 
fair sized Star Hopper.
Desmonus sighed as she relaxed against the table, moving her wrists and 
ankles now and again to loosen the straps.
She was hungry and needed to feed, and there had to be a bot or two around 
this place that would eagerly offer up a pint or two of their mech-fluid to 
a hungry fembot.*
